description:
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is all about people. As a not for profit organisation, everything we do is about looking after the individual. To support and encourage them to be as healthy as they can be. With a holistic approach to health and wellbeing we connect diagnosis and treatment, prevention and fitness across one, nationwide network. And to provide that groundbreaking service we bring together the most talented and dedicated professionals in one, valued community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest healthcare charity. We’re balancing our social values with strong business discipline to help the UK get healthy and stay that way. We’re all about great people, too – recruiting and nurturing talent in a supportive, development-led setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The person - We are looking for a flexible and motivated qualified NMC/HPC registered practitioner to support our existing team. You will deliver high quality care to our patients working in our theatre department you will be working with patients from a wide variety of specialties which will broaden your skills and experience. You must have good oral &amp; written skills, the ability to direct &amp; support the non-qualified staff &amp; the desire to provide the best possible care to all our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
